File: A man walks past the words "Coronavirus" painted on a wall, amid the spread of the coronavirus disease (COVID-19) outbreak, in Soweto, South Africa, May 31, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - Close to 9,000 new infections have been reported, bringing the number of positive cases in South Africa close to 200,000. The Health Department also reported a further 173 COVID-19 related deaths. SA's COVID-19 death toll is now at 3,199. READ: Eswatini cabinet in isolation after minister contracts COVID-19 The Health Department recorded 71 new deaths in Gauteng, 40 in the Western Cape, 29 in the Eastern Cape and 21 in KZN. The Free State reported 10 deaths and the Northern Cape recorded two. READ: SA Lockdown: Grades R, 6, and 11 to return to school on Monday Just over 93,000 of those who tested positive, have recovered. Health Media Release 5 July 2020 v1 (1) by eNCA.com on Scribd  - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.